President Obama issued a statement praising Congressman Rush Holt on his retirement after 15 years in Congress. Holt was commended for his dedication to building a better future and improving the lives of the people he represented, particularly veterans. As a research physicist and the second of his kind to be elected to Congress, Holt played a crucial role in advancing innovation in America. He consistently advocated for funding science education and basic research, leaving a lasting legacy in laboratories, universities, and classrooms. The President expressed gratitude to Holt for his leadership and service, extending well wishes to him, his wife Margaret, and their family.